# Coding

## Stack
- Backend: `Backend/src/` — Node/Express, Mongoose models in `core/` and `modules/`.
- Frontend: `Frontend/src/` — React, API clients in `services/api/`.

## Rules
- Extend existing functions/components; copy local patterns (imports, naming, error shape).
- Backend errors: use existing error classes/handlers in `core/auth/errors.js` and `middleware/errorHandler.js`.
- Frontend API: add methods to the matching file under `services/api/`, export from `index.js` if needed.
- Identity/driver flows: `Backend/src/core/identity/`, `Frontend/src/services/api/identity.js`.

## Avoid
- New helpers for one use, verbose comments, speculative error handling.
- Touching unrelated modules in the same change.
